[00:08.30]Forty days in the desert, dust on His skin
[00:12.86]Silence so loud, hear the war within
[00:17.41]Hunger in the body, Spirit standing tall
[00:21.97]Enemy whispers like he’s doing Him a favor, not a fall
[00:26.53]“If You’re really the Son, prove who You are
[00:31.08]Turn these stones to bread, show Your power, go far”
[00:35.64]But He stood on the Word, not the need of the flesh
[00:40.19]He didn’t bow to the moment, He trusted what’s next
[00:44.75]Every promise twisted, every lie dressed clean
[00:49.31]But truth don’t bend when temptation screams
[00:53.86]Stones don’t become bread when faith takes the stand
[00:58.42]Man don’t live by hunger but the Word in His hands
[01:02.97]From the peak to the pit, He never let go
[01:07.53]Kingdoms were offered, but He chose the cross road
[01:12.09]He said no to the crown, said yes to the will
[01:16.64]Victory whispered on a desert hill
[01:21.20]On the highest rooftop, wind in His face
[01:25.75]“Jump and the angels will catch You in grace”
[01:30.31]Scripture misquoted, truth turned thin
[01:34.87]But God’s Word ain’t a tool for the pride of men
[01:39.42]“You don’t test the Father, you trust His name”
[01:43.98]Not chasing spectacle, not playing games
[01:48.53]Strength in surrender, power restrained
[01:53.09]Heaven was watching, hell felt the pain
[01:57.65]Stones don’t become bread when faith takes the stand
[02:02.20]Man don’t live by hunger but the Word in His hands
[02:06.76]From the peak to the pit, He never let go
[02:11.31]Kingdoms were offered, but He chose the cross road
[02:15.87]He said no to the crown, said yes to the will
[02:20.43]Victory whispered on a desert hill
[02:24.98]Bow once, rule all, just worship me
[02:29.54]But the Lamb don’t kneel to the enemy
[02:34.09]Every knee gonna bow, every tongue confess
[02:38.65]But not by shortcuts, not by compromise stress
[02:43.21]Written Word sharp like a two-edged blade
[02:47.76]Devil left defeated when the Son obeyed
[02:52.32]Stones don’t become bread, lies don’t win
[02:56.87]Truth stood firm and the war caved in
[03:01.43]Tempted in all ways, yet without sin
[03:05.99]The battle was loud but the victory was Him
[03:10.54]Angels came running, strength restored
[03:15.10]The desert bloomed when He spoke the Word
